# Hashed build assets must resolve to real files only. If one is missing
# (a stale client requesting an old hash after a deploy), return a real 404
# instead of falling through to the HTML shell below. Serving index.html for a
# .js/.css request makes the browser parse HTML as a module -> the chunk
# resolves with no `default` export and React.lazy crashes with
# "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'default')". A clean 404 lets
# the app's chunk-error recovery reload once against a fresh index.html.
/assets/*    /assets/:splat    404

# SPA fallback: serve the prebuilt shell for every app route in one hop.
# 200 (rewrite, not 301/302) = no redirect chain, single round trip.
/*    /index.html    200
